The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks for electrocardiogram (ECG) rhythm classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores the use of attention mechanisms to improve classification performance and provide interpretability, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of gating parameters in a CNN model, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
